med when the file is closed. This means you don’t need to call "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/FileAccess\/flush()"},{"type":"text","text":" manually before closing a file. Still, calling "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/FileAccess\/flush()","isActive":true},{"text":" can be used to ensure the data is safe even if the project crashes instead of being closed gracefully.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/FileAccess\/flush()","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/fileaccess\/flush()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"flush","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]}}}